---
import { siteConfig } from "../data/site";
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import SiteHeader from "../components/SiteHeader.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title={`About | ${siteConfig.title}`}>
  <div class="zone-a genesis-stage" style="padding-top: 8rem; padding-bottom: 6rem;">
    <SiteHeader />
    <div class="shell">
      <h1 class="text-gradient">Architectural Profile</h1>
      <p class="lead" style="max-width: 60ch;">Writing and building at the intersection of Protocol Engineering, Agent Governance, and AI-native software delivery.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="zone-b page-body" style="padding: 6rem 0;">
    <div class="shell about-split">
      <!-- Left: Specs -->
      <aside class="about-specs">
        <div class="glass-panel-light" style="padding: 2.5rem; position: sticky; top: 8rem;">
          <span class="eyebrow">Specifications</span>
          <dl class="spec-list">
            <div>
              <dt>Identity</dt>
              <dd>Jearon Wang</dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>Role</dt>
              <dd>Protocol Architect</dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>Focus</dt>
              <dd>Agent Runtimes // Cognitive OS</dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>Location</dt>
              <dd>Remote // Async-Native</dd>
            </div>
          </dl>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <!-- Right: Narrative -->
      <article class="about-narrative">
        <section class="narrative-section">
          <h2>The Thesis</h2>
          <p>The industry has spent the last two years solving for <em>capability</em>. We have models that can reason, tools that can execute, and agents that can plan. But we do not yet have <em>reliability</em>.</p>
          <p>My work focuses on the protocol layer—the invisible structures that ensure autonomous work is auditable, governable, and bit-identical in its proof of delivery.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="narrative-section" style="margin-top: 4rem;">
          <h2>Background</h2>
          <p>I operate as a Protocol Architect. This means I don't just build agents; I build the runtimes that bound them. From the Machine Priority Legibility Protocol (MPLP) to the SoloCrew implementation apparatus, my focus is on the "how" of reliable delivery.</p>
        </section>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-split {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 340px 1fr;
    gap: 6rem;
  }
  .spec-list {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }
  .spec-list dt {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent-electric);
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }
  .spec-list dd {
    margin: 0;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: #0f172a;
  }
  .about-narrative h2 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    color: #0f172a;
  }
  .about-narrative p {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: #475569;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .about-split {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 4rem;
    }
    .about-specs {
      order: 2;
    }
  }
</style>
